desc:Load-and-Go Psycho MultiSampler (FluxBridge + tape + hybrid + granular v49-posteq-solo-fix)
tags:instrument sampler ui
options:gmem=SampleGroupSync
// #GFX_RESIZE: responsive

// v48 CompileFixStrings: removes illegal string parameter from GroupSync hash helper; keeps JSFX functions top-down-safe.
// v47 DeCrustCompileFix: restores cubic_mid() before the DeCrust curvature helper uses it.
// v46 CleanDeCrust: Shift+Clean adds an FFT-512 spectral-kurtosis decrust mode for crunchy/crusty SFX; FFT work runs only while the hidden mode is active.
// v45 GroupSync Ordering: uses host track_name()/track_name_seq() for default group naming, shares peers via gmem, and adds strict drag-rank ordering for Granular input texture triggers.
// v44 TextureInjection GateFix: dry input is explicitly restored at output, and Granular Input Env uses a dBFS soft-knee envelope with no retrigger while held.
// v42 InputEnv: Shift+drag Grain arms Granular-only audio input triggering; input is used as detector/envelope to scale generated texture and auto-release safely when silence returns.
// v41 DynExpand: Shift+drag Dynamics controls hidden Expansion, a transient-aware contrast/punch separator that lowers low-level material and can exaggerate attacks without adding a knob.
// v40 CleanScrub: Clean is upgraded into a stronger transient-protected multiband de-noise/de-bed path with SNR-aware gating, sustained-noise detection, high-band hiss targeting, and fail-fast obvious high settings.
// v39 RoomScrub: Room Tame is upgraded into a stronger transient-protected multiband de-room/de-smear path with per-band late/diffuse detection, side wash reduction, and fail-fast obvious high settings.
// v38 DenormalGuard: adds internal anti-denormal keepalive/zapping, gates silent visual analyzers, decimates the visual spectrum analyzer 4x, and keeps v37 Granular perf gates intact.
// v37 PerfGate: Grain corpus build is lazy/gated to Granular mode, dead learned-flow training is disabled, and Granular runtime selection plus 32-slot grain scans are gated so Raw/Tape/Hybrid avoid corpus work and Hybrid avoids Granular slot cost.
// v36 GranStretch EventScale + PeakPack Pro: in Granular only, Stretch is repurposed from fast purposeful grains at 1x toward slower, larger, more coherent event playback at 4x; Raw/Tape/Hybrid Stretch behavior is preserved.
// v35 MacroGrain OLAGlue + PeakPack Pro: Granular adds 1ms/10ms/100ms/1000ms-scale load-time corpus analysis, permits event-scale macro-grains for coherent SFX, and smooths OLA/spawn edges to reduce clicks and gaps.
// v49 PostEQSoloFix: restores Ctrl+click/drag temporary Post-EQ band/cut solo audition.
// v28 SpectrumPrePost: Post-Processing now draws detailed pre-EQ and post-EQ spectra on one shared scale.
// v27 SpectrumDetail: Post-EQ spectrum uses a 96-bin resonant analyzer and thin trace drawing instead of a broad lowpass-difference blob.
// v26 SpectrumContrast: Post-EQ spectrum underlay is brighter, adaptive, and easier to read on quiet material.
// v25 BandQCal: Band 1/2/3 Q is calibrated to the actual peaking-biquad response; default Q is tighter and less absurdly wide.
// v24 PostEQ QFix: HPF/LPF Q now produces visible and audible cutoff resonance, including 6 dB/oct mode.
// v23 FreeBand PostEQ: three free parametric bands plus HPF/LPF, graph control, Q/slope gestures, and spectrum underlay.
// v22 PostEQ removed the Shaper page and kept Processing as final-output EQ.
// v19 AutoRelease: sample-tail analysis adds a release floor and graceful EOF/tail-grain fades.
// v18 FormantDrive: Shift+drag Pitch controls an audible hidden transient-safe formant/resonance shift.
// v13 CrossFlow: keeps v12 learned continuation, but prevents same-take reconstruction loops.
// Slot 0 is the load-and-go sample bank.
// Use the filename slot UI for this instrument and choose Open Multiple... on slot 0.
// #FILE: Sample Bank {Open Multiple... loads the whole bank into slot 0; the bank auto-rescans when the selection changes.}
filename:0,sample.wav

// #HELP: # Sample
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## What it is
// #HELP: Sample is a load-and-go psycho multisampler: load files into slot 0, play notes, and shape the bank with compact macro controls.
// #HELP: v15 BrightCal uses a filterbank brightness meter and bank-aware Color scaling.
// #HELP: v16 FocusCal makes Focus bank-aware: high attack-focus banks soften harder and clarify more cautiously; dull banks clarify harder and soften more cautiously.
// #HELP: v18 strengthens Shift+drag Pitch formant shifting: audible spectral-envelope warp plus resonance drive, still transient-protected.
// #HELP: v19 AutoRelease analyzes each sample tail, extends too-short MIDI releases when needed, and fades source endings so EOF does not chop.
// #HELP: v28 SpectrumPrePost shows both pre-EQ and post-EQ spectra with a cleaner high-resolution analyzer.
// #HELP: v27 SpectrumDetail makes the Post-Processing spectrum sharper with a higher-resolution resonant analyzer and thinner trace display.
// #HELP: v26 SpectrumContrast makes the Post-Processing spectrum underlay brighter and easier to read on quiet material.
// #HELP: v45 GroupSync adds decentralized same-name Sampler coordination: Auto Track Name grouping, lowest-ID leader display, and a strict drag-rank order editor for texture-injection triggers.
// #HELP: v29 GrainCorpus builds a load-time grain/event corpus so Granular can transform both single long sources and multi-source banks without doing descriptor analysis at playback time.
// #HELP: v33 EnvTrajectory teaches Granular to follow learned corpus energy motion so phrases have rises, falls, crests, and decay instead of flat wet grain beds.
// #HELP: v44 TextureInjection GateFix makes Granular Input Env a true texture-injection path: dry input is passed through untouched, while a dBFS soft-knee input envelope triggers and amplitude-shapes only the generated Granular layer.
// #HELP: v42 InputEnv adds Shift+drag Grain for Granular-only audio-trigger amount: incoming audio can trigger and envelope-scale the generated granular texture.
// #HELP: v46 CleanDeCrust adds Shift+drag Clean as an FFT-512 spectral-kurtosis decrust mode for crunchy/crusty SFX. It is intentionally fail-fast at high values and the FFT path is inactive unless the hidden mode is nonzero.
// #HELP: v40 CleanScrub makes Clean a stronger general cleanup control: it detects low-SNR/sustained bed noise per band, suppresses hiss and static tails harder, preserves attacks, and becomes deliberately obvious at high values.
// #HELP: v39 RoomScrub makes Room Tame a stronger general de-room control: it detects late/diffuse band energy, trims low-mid/presence room wash, narrows roomy side smear, and protects attacks.
// #HELP: v38 DenormalGuard protects internal recursive filters/analyzers from near-zero denormal stalls, gates silent spectrum analysis, and preserves v37 Granular gating.
// #HELP: v34 MultiScaleEventGrains analyzes short/mid/long windows at corpus-build time and lets Granular use event-sized grains when the source material wants continuity.
// #HELP: v35 MacroGrain OLAGlue extends this to micro/short/mid/long/ultra windows, allowing coherent slow material to use 100 ms to 1 s grains while smoothing OLA starts, normalization, and long-grain window shape.
// #HELP: v37 PerfGate lazily builds the GrainCorpus only when Granular mode is active or selected, disables obsolete learned-flow training, and caps Hybrid grain scans below the Granular-only 32-slot pool.
// #HELP: v36 GranStretch repurposes Stretch inside Granular only: 1x keeps the current fast purposeful grain feel, while higher values bias toward slower, larger, more coherent event playback.
// #HELP: v25 BandQCal makes Band 1/2/3 Q use the actual peaking-EQ response and changes the default from ultra-wide to generous.
// #HELP: v24 PostEQ QFix makes HPF/LPF Q visible and audible as cutoff resonance.
// #HELP: v23 FreeBand PostEQ adds a spectrum-underlaid final EQ: HPF, LPF, and three draggable parametric bands with Q and cutoff slope control.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Quick start
// #HELP: 1. Insert Sample. 2. On slot 0, choose Open Multiple... and select files. 3. Play MIDI notes. 4. Choose Random, Sequence, or Walk. 5. Shape with Envelope, Playback, Post-Processing, Clean, Room Tame, Push, and Output.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Selection modes
// #HELP: Random picks from the full bank with anti-repeat weighting. Sequence steps through loaded files. Walk bridges from the previous sample using brightness, focus, transient richness, length, pitch confidence, body span, and tail span.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Envelope
// #HELP: Attack, Hold, Decay, Sustain, and Release shape each trigger. Shift+Wheel on Attack, Decay, or Release changes slope from -100% to +100%; 0% is linear. Release is also protected by sample-dependent AutoRelease when a source would otherwise chop; Shift+drag Release changes hidden Tail Grace.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Playback engines
// #HELP: Raw plays the source directly. Tape uses the slower/heavier rate path. Hybrid keeps the head direct, sustains from body grains, can borrow matched tails, and can hand off Release level/body phase into the next Attack. Granular uses a load-time analyzed grain corpus: long files become many searchable micro-events, multi-source banks become one shared grain field, and playback uses anchor/texture/spice streams, phrase + envelope trajectories, corpus continuity, source-adaptive overlap, restrained swells, release blooms, and grain-level decorrelation.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Cleanup and depth
// #HELP: Clean is a transient-protected de-noise/de-bed macro: low values clean hiss/static tails gently, high values aggressively scrub low-SNR sustained noise and become obvious quickly. Shift+drag Clean controls DeCrust, a hidden FFT-512 spectral-kurtosis crust repair mode for crunchy SFX; it is bypassed completely at 0. Room Tame is a transient-protected de-room/de-smear macro: low values restrain late room wash, high values make the correction obvious quickly. Push is a salience budget: higher values push the instrument farther back, with 100% as extreme background placement.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Post-Processing
// #HELP: The Post-Processing panel is a final-output EQ editor with pre/post spectrum overlay, draggable HPF/LPF cutoffs, and three free parametric bands. Drag bands horizontally for frequency and vertically for gain; wheel adjusts Q; Shift+Wheel on HPF/LPF changes slope; Ctrl+click/drag temporarily solos the selected band/cut for auditioning.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Tone and feel
// #HELP: Color warms/brightens. Focus softens/clarifies. Shift+drag Focus adjusts hidden Peak Pack: negative can flatten detected spectral maxima, positive can push resonant maxima. Shift+drag Pitch adjusts hidden formant/resonance shift. Shift+drag Grain adjusts hidden Granular Input amount: dry input passes through, and its dBFS envelope injects/scales generated Granular texture. Width spreads safely. Liveliness adds variation. Truth moves from matched behavior toward raw sample individuality. Dynamics adds density with protection; Shift+drag Dynamics adds hidden Expansion for punch/space contrast.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## FluxBridge
// #HELP: When the fixed FluxBridge CC lane block is present, Sample adds subtle motion-driven tone, focus, width, pan, and body contour while protecting transient-rich hits.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Best uses
// #HELP: Fast one-shot banks, found-sound instruments, texture instruments, sketching, and exploratory sound design.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## Wrong tool
// #HELP: Use a traditional multisampler when you need exact key zones, velocity-layer authoring, or realistic note-by-note recreation.
// #HELP:
// #HELP: ## In one sentence
// #HELP: Sample turns a loose bank of audio files into a playable, variable instrument with almost no setup.

slider1:0<0,1,1{idle,rescan}>--Force rescan slot 0
slider2:3<0.1,500,0.1>--Attack (ms)
slider3:110<1,5000,1>--Decay (ms)
